body:
Currently `HiveSource` uses `HivePartition`'s createTime to check if it is within lookback. This can cause reprocessing when old source partitions are dropped and recreated.
This change is to use the logical time represented by partition's name for lookback.

@abti can you review?

* Move enum AbstractJobLauncher.MULTI_TASK_ATTEMPT_COMMIT_POLICY to GobblinMultiTaskAttempt since even the name suggests it pertains to GobblinMultiTaskAttempt; Rename to CommitPolicy to conform to the naming conventions.
* Move static AbstractJobLauncher.runWorkUnits methods to GobblinMultiTaskAttempt since those deal mostly with GobblinMultiTaskAttempt.

@ydai1124 can you review?

There is a slight race condition in KafkaJobMonitorTest, where monitor.awaitExactlyNSpecs(2) can pass right after job1:2 is added and before job2:2 is added. In that case, the assert Assert.assertEquals(monitor.getJobSpecs().get(new URI("job2")).getVersion(), "2") might fail.

This changes the order of adding the new JobSpecs.

